# Cloudflare Pages routing for Talle Furniture Mart frontend.
#
# Order matters: more specific rules first, SPA fallback last.

# === API proxy ===
# Every /api/* request from the browser is rewritten by Cloudflare's edge
# to hit the Render backend server-to-server. Two big wins:
#  1. The browser only ever talks to talle-furniture.pages.dev (same
#     origin) → no CORS, and Indian mobile carriers can't transparently
#     proxy / block onrender.com IPs because the phone never connects
#     to that host directly.
#  2. Cloudflare's Mumbai edge POP is closer to Indian users than
#     Render's region → faster perceived latency on every request.
# The 200 status code makes this a rewrite (the URL bar stays as
# talle-furniture.pages.dev/api/...) not a 30x redirect.
/api/*  https://toy-mall.onrender.com/api/:splat  200

# Proxy the sitemap from the backend so search engines see it on the
# canonical frontend domain. The 200 status makes this a rewrite, not a
# redirect — Google fetches it from tallefurnituremart.com/sitemap.xml directly.
/sitemap.xml  https://toy-mall.onrender.com/sitemap.xml  200

# Single-page-app fallback. Every other URL serves index.html so the
# React router can handle it (otherwise refreshing /product/foo 404s).
/*  /index.html  200
